josm-mapillary-plugin API

Packages 
Package Description
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary
The main package in which all core-code (so at the moment all code) resides.
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.actions
Actions that are normally attached to a button or a menu item and are then executed to manipulate the MapillaryLayer when the button is clicked.
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.cache
This package is all about caching resources downloaded from mapillary.com for faster access to those resources in the future.
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.gui
The GUI components that are special to the mapillary plugin.
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.history
This package deals with keeping a history of actions the user performed to allow for undoing and redoing these actions.
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.history.commands
The commands that the user can execute, which are recorded in the undo/redo-log.
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.io.download
Classes for downloading images, sequences and image metadata like traffic signs from mapillary.com .
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.io.export
Classes for exporting images that were downloaded from mapillary.com .
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.mode
The different modes that the MapillaryLayer can be in.
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.oauth
Everything related to signing users in and out of Mapillary.
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.traffico
Components for painting traffic signs with the help of the traffico icon font.
org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.utils
Utility classes for simplifying recurring tasks throughout the project.
